Note:  CO2 instrument found to have a 4-s time constant,
greatly reducing frequency response.  The manufacturers claimed
that we didn't observe a 10 Hz frequency response in IFC-I
because they had incorporated the 0.05-s time constant amplifier
into the back panel output labeled "4-s."  The instrument was,
therefore, modified for IFC-II to select the output from the 4-s
channel.  Spectral analysis of flight data showed that the data
collected from the 4-s channel had an approximately 0.2 Hz
frequency response.  This implied that the amplifier improvements
had not been properly implemented.  Affected research flights are
RF09 and RF10.

